snippet.textDisplay:
Hard to dominate against what was a well organised team of committed players. They had obviously done their research and played to strategically nullify Trent and Robertson for large parts of the game.

Despite the strength and organization of Flamenco, Liverpool had the best chances. We should have made better use of the chances we had. Bobby who did had the best chances made amends with a sublime goal in the end.

Mane was immense throughout the entire game but not one Liverpool player had a bad game. It would be hard to think of a moment in the game where any Liverpool player was out of position during the game.

Klopp has built a team of great players all of which have grown as they matured within the team.

They now play with such belief that any & every player in the world would want to be part of this great team.

This trophy is a real bonus. 🏆.

The goal for this season is the Premiership. We still have a long way to go. We need to be mindful of injuries and how that might impact on the the remainder of the season. Wishing Ox a speedy recovery.

Remember #YNWA. ❤️
